	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Answer - your own emulator. Start by reading a 6502 CPU document and try to do a draft of CPU opcodes operations. Then, start programming them. Later, you create an environment.
<br />
<br />To compile, I use MinGW + Allegro + DevCpp as UI. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


