		<td><b>VirtualNES looks modern and buildable</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was able to get VirtualNES (by Norix) built and running.
<br />
<br />It is in C++ and the source is modern Win32 for Visual Stuido.
<br />
<br />The only downside is that the comments are mixed Japanese and english.
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://virtuanes.s1.xrea.com:8080/index.php">http://virtuanes.s1.xrea.com:8080/index.php</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Some good featues:
<br />  1. Continiously updated real time memory dump 
<br />  2. name table viewer
<br />  3. scrolling viewer

		

